programmes.show_description: How do they grow nearly 200,000 tonnes of mushrooms a year in the mushroom capital of the world? And, how do they make billions of life-saving gloves?
How do they mine a million tonnes of fertiliser from below the sea? How do they hand print millions of colourful clothes using the art of batik?
Audi Coupe. Mike finds the perfect starter classic, a 1989 Audi Coupe. This rare car has a low mileage, but it's failed its MOT. The guys fix it up before a test drive in Cornwall.
VW Corrado V2. Mike finds a 1992 Corrado G60 smothered in aftermarket mods. Parts are rare and superchargers can be costly, but Elvis determines to get this risky project done.
Volvo 164. Henry and Fuzz visit David in Swansea to restore his 1970 Volvo 164, a sturdy classic known for luxury, durability, and timeless Swedish design.
More everyday items go under the microscope. How are objects including basketry sculptures and coffee roasters made?
More everyday items go under the microscope. How are objects including reconditioned sander drums and lithographs made?
Teleshopping.
Teleshopping.
Sonnaz and Rachael revive a pair of chairs that are the owner's last links to her Dutch heritage. Plus, Will works on an army officer's military campaign chest.
Drew and Tee head to a grade II listed mansion in Lincolnshire. The house is packed with items and Drew haggles for a superb 19th century chair and a decorated chinoiserie mirror.
The boys stop at a salvage yard which Drew hails as the best in the country. They find a pair of beautifully crafted sundials and an overthrow believed to be from Belvoir Castle.
Chris And Vince. Paul Mackie and the team try to find the causes of a two-year dry streak that threatens to end the dreams of rookie prospectors Chris Moore and Vince Federici.
The Veterans. Paul Mackie's team have just six days to help a team of ex-servicemen become skilled mobile goldminers and reach their dream of funding a veteran's charity.
Desperate Times, Desperate Measures. Justin and Becky risk their lives underground. Plus, opal hunting legend Col Duff is back, hunting long forgotten treasure.
Battling Back. The Fire Crew's season rests on a knife-edge as they battle their way back from a disastrous setback. Plus, the Opal Queen mines rock hard walls alone.
Sonnaz and Rachael revive a pair of chairs that are the owner's last links to her Dutch heritage. Plus, Will works on an army officer's military campaign chest.
MG MGA. Henry and Fuzz visit Colin in Hertfordshire to revive his faded MG MGA - a once-glorious 1950s sports car that's been silent for years.
Henry and Fuzz are back in Durham visiting a passionate collector of vintage cars and automobilia, where a Dot three-wheeled motorcycle catches their eye.
Henry and Fuzz are at a farm in Gloucester looking through a collection of tractors. There, they unearth some historic items from the 1910s and '20s, but can they be restored?
Selling Up Before Baby Comes. With just a month before her due date, Gem and Tom ask Angus to visit their 16th century Suffolk home. Plus, a retired couple needs help with a downsize.
The UK's Biggest Collection. A couple with a collection of dishes asks Angus to sell them to fund a trip to Australia. Plus, Angus finds a huge fire engine part in a living room.
Natasha and Phil continue their antiquing adventure around the Scottish Borders, picking up a fish service, a sandwich box and a silver kettle.
Tash and Phil hunt for antiques in Scotland. While Tash goes French with some candlesticks, Phil reverts to type and buys old, weighty farm troughs.
Tickled Pink. The Cog respray an Aston Martin Lagonda a shocking pink for Europe's biggest car collector. Richard's daughter Izzy discovers a passion for racing.
In The Trenches. The Misfits return to their claim and find it's been soaked by torrential rain. The Opal Lovers dig a deep trench on their Digger's Gully claim.
Beware Of The Locals. Camille and Hannah hunt on Springbank Island in the middle of Lake Burley Griffin. Andrew and Mish make some illuminating finds.
How do they turn thousands of tonnes of basmati rice into millions of microwaveable meals? How do they craft beautiful mechanical singing birds?
How do they make an almost invisible hearing aid that connects wirelessly to a phone? How do they build the carriages for London's new underground railway?
How do they build remote-controlled underwater robots to do jobs too dangerous for human divers? How do they make the world's most cuddly teddy bears?
Learn how platinum cleans your car's exhaust fumes, and find out how they build a space station 360 kilometres above the earth?
Ford Fiesta Mk1. To celebrate the series' 20th anniversary, Mike and Elvis set out to restore a Ford Fiesta Mark 1 and stage the show's largest ever car meet.
Peugeot 205. A Peugeot 205 T16 inspires Mike to upgrade its under-powered UK counterpart for a track race. Can Mike's 205 Rallye compete with a Eurospec Peugeot?
MG MGA. Henry and Fuzz visit Colin in Hertfordshire to revive his faded MG MGA - a once-glorious 1950s sports car that's been silent for years.
More everyday items go under the microscope. How are objects including calissons and diving watercrafts made?
More everyday items go under the microscope. How are objects including game tables and art glass wall sconces made?

Teleshopping.
A widower asks Mark and the team to fix his beloved transistor radio. Julie and Amanda work on a giant teddy bear, while Steve revamps a skeleton clock.
Scotland Special. Drew and Tee are on a trip through the Scottish Lowlands. Their first stop is Buittle Castle, where one item compels Drew to pay Â£100 more than the asking price.
Hats Off For A Deal. Drew is surprised by the items he picks up at a quirky shop in County Durham. Later, he must give up his hat to secure a deal on two extraordinarily rare items.
Jarrod Crosbie. Paul Mackie's mine makeover team deal with hardship and heartbreak as they help up-and-coming prospector Jarrod Crosbie overcome a barrage of setbacks.
Nathan And Steve. The team set out to install a full-scale hard rock mining operation and deliver a potentially life changing payday for rookies, Nathan Malatesta and Steve Ogilvie.
Make Or Break. Justin tackles a deal that could make or break him. And, the Boulder Boys race to save their claim from a monsoon flood while the Cooke Brothers hit pay dirt.
Last Chance. The end of the mining season is near. The Rookies gamble their hopes on one last haul of opal and the Opal Queen makes a final desperate dig.
A widower asks Mark and the team to fix his beloved transistor radio. Julie and Amanda work on a giant teddy bear, while Steve revamps a skeleton clock.
Standard 14. Henry and Fuzz head to Bristol to help Russell revive his 1947 Standard 14: a post-war classic with charm, history, and plenty of hidden troubles.
Presenter Henry Cole and mechanic Fuzz Townshend hit the road to find, buy and make a profit from the UK's abandoned automotive gems.
Presenter Henry Cole and mechanic Fuzz Townshend hit the road to find, buy and make a profit from the UK's abandoned automotive gems.
Yorkshire Mice And Russian Dolls. Cancer survivor, Claire wants to downsize to free up some cash and have fun. Plus, Clive needs funding for his mum's care home costs.
From Russia With Love. A widow returns from Italy, bringing with her Soviet propaganda. While Victorian gadgets sees Angus geek-out over tech from a bygone age.
In Scotland, experts Natasha and Philip find rare first edition books, watercolours by local artists and a plate of delicious homemade scones.
Natasha and Phil shop in Northern Ireland before an auction in Wales. An unexpected bidding frenzy helps one expert take the win!
Railway Relics & A Harley Hog. Angus steams into a train treasure trove while helping a bereaved daughter, then hopes to turn a campervan dream into reality with a Harley sale.
The team take on an ornate wooden piano stool that holds treasured memories. Horologist Steve repairs a vintage car speedometer, and a baby's wicker crib is restored.
The team restores a tiny bird brooch that's been in a family for four generations. Plus, a rag doll from WWII called Chiefy is made fit for service again.
Learn how they turn a family car into a tough rally car, and how they make titanium, the metal that the modern aerospace industry relies on?
How do submarine crews survive submerged beneath the ocean for months at a time? Plus, how do crash test dummies make driving safer?
